{"id": 6577, "title": "Ticket #6577: Incorrect VM Universe MemoryUsage", "description": "<blockquote>\nBy default VM Universe jobs set the <code>MemoryUsage</code> to <code>VM_Memory</code>, which is the amount of memory left to start VMs on the entire machine. The more appropriate attribute to reference would be <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ImageSize\" title=\"Image Size\">ImageSize</a></span> (with conversion from KB to MB).\n\n<p>Brian Lin writes:\n\n</p><p></p><div class=\"verbatim\">\n<pre>In our experience at CHTC with KVM, ResidentSetSize doesn't get updated.\n</pre></div>\n</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2018-Mar-01 11:52:38 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE_REVIEW</strong> change looks good. although the version field in param_info.in is not the last time we changed the value, it's the first version of HTCondor for which the knob has meaning.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2018-Mar-09 11:18:08 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>DOC REVIEW:</strong> Looks good.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Mar-01 14:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/4e5e96c82c83235b6f1d3956826ca1d018673d08\">[54407]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6577\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6577'); return false;\" title=\"Incorrect VM Universe MemoryUsage\">#6577</a></span>) Undo stupid change to version field.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Feb-26 13:12</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span>